<segment id="1" parent="1001" relname="span">Know Yourself</segment>
<segment id="2" parent="1" relname="circumstance">when You Do n&apos;t Have a Mother</segment>
<segment id="3" parent="1003" relname="span">Understanding yourself is often a little easier</segment>
<segment id="4" parent="3" relname="condition">if you know where you came from .</segment>
<segment id="5" parent="1006" relname="condition">But if you do not have a mother in your life ,</segment>
<segment id="6" parent="1006" relname="span">this can be a part of your life story</segment>
<segment id="7" parent="6" relname="elaboration">that you will never know quite the same way as other people .</segment>
<segment id="8" parent="1008" relname="span">And that can leave an emptiness in a person &apos;s heart .</segment>
<segment id="9" parent="8" relname="elaboration">It can make simple questions of connection a mystery .</segment>
<segment id="10" parent="1010" relname="contrast">But whether your mother is dead ,</segment>
<segment id="11" parent="1010" relname="contrast">or you were adopted by another family as a child ,</segment>
<segment id="12" parent="1012" relname="span">or for some other reason your mother is not present in your life --</segment>
<segment id="13" parent="1014" relname="attribution">it helps to know</segment>
<segment id="14" parent="1014" relname="span">that there are ways</segment>
<segment id="15" parent="1015" relname="span">to make connections</segment>
<segment id="16" parent="15" relname="elaboration">that can help you understand yourself .</segment>
<segment id="17" parent="1017" relname="span">This article will teach you how to know yourself ,</segment>
<segment id="18" parent="1018" relname="contrast">despite losing your mother</segment>
<segment id="19" parent="1018" relname="contrast">or never knowing her .</segment>
<segment id="20" parent="1020" relname="preparation">Steps</segment>
<segment id="21" parent="1021" relname="span">Remember your childhood memories of your mother ,</segment>
<segment id="22" parent="21" relname="condition">if you have any .</segment>
<segment id="23" parent="1024" relname="span">Recall what you can about the time</segment>
<segment id="24" parent="23" relname="elaboration">you spent with your mother .</segment>
<segment id="25" parent="1025" relname="span">All memories are precious ,</segment>
<segment id="26" parent="1027" relname="span">even those</segment>
<segment id="27" parent="26" relname="elaboration">that make us sad or angry ,</segment>
<segment id="28" parent="1028" relname="span">even those</segment>
<segment id="29" parent="28" relname="elaboration">that seem pointless .</segment>
<segment id="30" parent="1031" relname="attribution">You may only recall vague details about your mother , her smell ,</segment>
<segment id="31" parent="1031" relname="span">the way</segment>
<segment id="32" parent="1033" relname="attribution">she sang to you ,</segment>
<segment id="33" parent="1033" relname="span">the books</segment>
<segment id="34" parent="1034" relname="joint">she read to you ,</segment>
<segment id="35" parent="1035" relname="span">the things</segment>
<segment id="36" parent="35" relname="elaboration">she told you off for even .</segment>
<segment id="37" parent="1022" relname="joint">All of these have influenced you ,</segment>
<segment id="38" parent="1038" relname="span">and , they are still in your head ,</segment>
<segment id="39" parent="1040" relname="attribution">so something in your brain hung onto those memories ,</segment>
<segment id="40" parent="1040" relname="same_unit">what you remember</segment>
<segment id="41" parent="1041" relname="span">is part of what makes you unique , part of what makes you you ,</segment>
<segment id="42" parent="41" relname="elaboration">a way for you to know yourself .</segment>
<segment id="43" parent="1022" relname="joint">Ask others to tell you their memories of your mother ,</segment>
<segment id="44" parent="45" relname="condition">whether you have any memories of your own or not ,</segment>
<segment id="45" parent="1044" relname="span">you can ask others what they know of her .</segment>
<segment id="46" parent="1048" relname="condition">If you lost your mother</segment>
<segment id="47" parent="1049" relname="circumstance">when you were older ,</segment>
<segment id="48" parent="1049" relname="span">you might like to find out about what your mother was like at your age ,</segment>
<segment id="49" parent="48" relname="elaboration">be that twelve , twenty , thirty-six , forty or any other age .</segment>
<segment id="50" parent="51" relname="attribution">You may be told</segment>
<segment id="51" parent="1050" relname="span">you are like your mother was .</segment>
<segment id="52" parent="1052" relname="span">You might hear stories</segment>
<segment id="53" parent="1053" relname="span">that you identify with or a tale</segment>
<segment id="54" parent="53" relname="elaboration">that makes you think ,</segment>
<segment id="55" parent="1055" relname="span">&quot; that &apos;s just what I would of done in that situation &quot; .</segment>
<segment id="56" parent="1057" relname="span">You can know yourself</segment>
<segment id="57" parent="56" relname="means">by identifying with others in this way ,</segment>
<segment id="58" parent="1059" relname="condition">and if you identify with your mother ,</segment>
<segment id="59" parent="1059" relname="span">you can feel a connection with her</segment>
<segment id="60" parent="59" relname="elaboration">even though she is no longer around .</segment>
<segment id="61" parent="1062" relname="attribution">You may be nothing like your mother ,</segment>
<segment id="62" parent="1062" relname="span">that &apos;s okay ,</segment>
<segment id="63" parent="62" relname="elaboration">you are yourself , not your mother .</segment>
<segment id="64" parent="1063" relname="joint">Knowing if you are not like her</segment>
<segment id="65" parent="66" relname="condition">or if you are just like her , or even a bit like her ,</segment>
<segment id="66" parent="1065" relname="span">all help you to know yourself and how alike or not you are to your mother .</segment>
<segment id="67" parent="1063" relname="joint">Recognize that what you experience</segment>
<segment id="68" parent="1069" relname="circumstance">and how you get through things ,</segment>
<segment id="69" parent="1069" relname="same_unit">good and bad ,</segment>
<segment id="70" parent="1069" relname="same_unit">are what make you &quot; you &quot; .</segment>
<segment id="71" parent="1073" relname="span">You may have turned out a completely different person</segment>
<segment id="72" parent="71" relname="condition">if your mother had been around for your whole life .</segment>
<segment id="73" parent="1074" relname="contrast">Her passing has had a huge influence on your life ,</segment>
<segment id="74" parent="1076" relname="attribution">however old or young you were</segment>
<segment id="75" parent="1077" relname="circumstance">when you lost her ,</segment>
<segment id="76" parent="1077" relname="span">whether you feel it or not ,</segment>
<segment id="77" parent="1079" relname="span">even if you had another supportive care giver</segment>
<segment id="78" parent="77" relname="elaboration">who took great care of you ,</segment>
<segment id="79" parent="1080" relname="sequence">your mother may have done things differently</segment>
<segment id="80" parent="1081" relname="same_unit">and raised a different you ,</segment>
<segment id="81" parent="1081" relname="same_unit">only different of course , not a better you , and not a worse one either .</segment>
<segment id="82" parent="1084" relname="span">You are the person</segment>
<segment id="83" parent="82" relname="elaboration">you are</segment>
<segment id="84" parent="1085" relname="joint">because of your mother &apos;s passing ,</segment>
<segment id="85" parent="1085" relname="joint">and that in and of itself is a piece of yourself .</segment>
<segment id="86" parent="1087" relname="span">In some case some your mother &apos;s information will be available</segment>
<segment id="87" parent="86" relname="circumstance">when you reach adulthood .</segment>
<segment id="88" parent="1088" relname="same_unit">For instance ,</segment>
<segment id="89" parent="1090" relname="condition">if you were adopted ,</segment>
<segment id="90" parent="1090" relname="span">you may be able to find out your birth information</segment>
<segment id="91" parent="90" relname="condition">if your family chooses to withhold that information .</segment>
<segment id="92" parent="1093" relname="condition">If there was a family tragedy such as a death ,</segment>
<segment id="93" parent="1093" relname="span">you may be able to gain information such as court records</segment>
<segment id="94" parent="93" relname="condition">if you choose to research it .</segment>
<segment id="95" parent="1094" relname="sequence">You may not be able to find out anything .</segment>
<segment id="96" parent="1094" relname="sequence">In some circumstances , you may not be able to find out anything about your mother .</segment>
<segment id="97" parent="1097" relname="same_unit">For instance ,</segment>
<segment id="98" parent="99" relname="condition">if you were abandoned as an infant ,</segment>
<segment id="99" parent="1098" relname="span">and no one knows your birth mother .</segment>
<segment id="100" parent="1099" relname="sequence">Or you were part of a closed adoption .</segment>
<segment id="101" parent="1100" relname="joint">You are you , whoever your mother is or was .</segment>
<segment id="102" parent="1103" relname="condition">Whatever you remember ,</segment>
<segment id="103" parent="1103" relname="contrast">find out ,</segment>
<segment id="104" parent="1104" relname="span">or otherwise know about your mother ,</segment>
<segment id="105" parent="1105" relname="span">remember that you are a unique , separate individual --</segment>
<segment id="106" parent="105" relname="elaboration">just like everyone else gets to discover .</segment>
<segment id="107" parent="1106" relname="joint">While it often helps to know your biological or family history ,</segment>
<segment id="108" parent="1106" relname="joint">in the end , your story is your own .</segment>
<segment id="109" parent="1109" relname="preparation">Warnings</segment>
<segment id="110" parent="1111" relname="span">Other people</segment>
<segment id="111" parent="110" relname="elaboration">who were close to your mother may get upset</segment>
<segment id="112" parent="1111" relname="elaboration">remembering things about her .</segment>
<segment id="113" parent="1114" relname="span">It could be because of the pain</segment>
<segment id="114" parent="113" relname="elaboration">of missing her ,</segment>
<segment id="115" parent="1116" relname="span">anger about hurtful things</segment>
<segment id="116" parent="115" relname="elaboration">she did ,</segment>
<segment id="117" parent="1117" relname="span">or confusion about choices</segment>
<segment id="118" parent="1118" relname="joint">she made --</segment>
<segment id="119" parent="1118" relname="joint">and perhaps all of these at the same time .</segment>
<segment id="120" parent="1120" relname="span">Remember that this has no reflection on you ,</segment>
<segment id="121" parent="1121" relname="joint">that it may be hard for others to talk about these things ,</segment>
<segment id="122" parent="1121" relname="joint">and you likely had no responsibility for your mother .</segment>
<segment id="123" parent="1123" relname="span">Be careful in dealing with mothers</segment>
<segment id="124" parent="123" relname="elaboration">that have had issues of responsibility , criminal activity , abuse towards others and so on .</segment>
<segment id="125" parent="1125" relname="span">Sometimes children are so eager to establish a relationship</segment>
<segment id="126" parent="1126" relname="span">they become blind to the fact</segment>
<segment id="127" parent="126" relname="elaboration">that such a relationship may have been broken for a reason .</segment>
<segment id="128" parent="1119" relname="sequence">Be careful .</segment>
<segment id="129" parent="130" relname="condition">If family members are reluctant to give out sensitive information about your mother ,</segment>
<segment id="130" parent="1129" relname="span">be respectful of their judgement .</segment>
<segment id="131" parent="1119" relname="sequence">Some information may not really be useful to you</segment>
<segment id="132" parent="1119" relname="sequence">and cause you or others unnecessary hurt .</segment>
<segment id="133" parent="1133" relname="span">Often information may be revealed to you</segment>
<segment id="134" parent="1134" relname="span">when you are judged mature enough</segment>
<segment id="135" parent="134" relname="purpose">to process the facts .</segment>
<segment id="136" parent="1135" relname="joint">You may get hurt</segment>
<segment id="137" parent="1135" relname="joint">depending on how it turns out .</segment>
